article_title: Election 2016: Two, Three or Even Four Parties
article_text:
Jim VandeHei’s proposal for a new political party headed by tech celebrities isn’t the answer to our political and cultural woes (“Bring on a Third-Party Candidate,” op-ed, April 26). The future of our nation depends more on the moral character and will of individual citizens than it does on electing enlightened “Dear Leaders.”

I believe that we are paying the price for my generation’s (baby boomer) excessive elevation of the self above all else. Duty (to God, family and country) has taken a cultural back seat to the quest...
